3.title: The Australian Grand Prix: Highlights
3.plot: The 2015 Australian Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race that was held on 15 March 2015 in Melbourne. The race was contested over fifty-eight laps of the Melbourne Grand Prix Circuit and was the first round of the 2015 FIA Formula One World Championship.The race marked the 80th race in the combined history of the Australian Grand Prix-which dates back to the 100 Miles Road Race of 1928-and the twentieth time the event was held at the Melbourne Grand Prix Circuit.
